{"text":"Buddhism also teaches to be skeptical, even of the beliefs of Buddhism itself. The goal of enlightenment after thousands of years of spiritual trial, can be thought of as a metaphor for the purpose of our singular short lives on Earth. 

We live our lives making moral decisions based on what we observe, or perceive, so when the end of our life comes, we stop making moral decisions. "We" don't exist anymore. One could interpret this void of reality as enlightenment. 

Open your mind to new ideas."}

{"text":"...I think the universe is much more unique than we perceive it to be. That we aren't getting the full picture.

Just as the ancient astronomers looked to the stars, and imagined dominating moral authorities who's sole purpose was to dictate their behavior, so to, are we naive to our artificial intelligence. It clouds our window to the natural world.

I think humans have based science and mathematics on an incomplete view of the cosmos. This is why I'm agnostic. It gives me hope for a soul..."}

